# Error Handling

## Custom Errors
- Implement `std::error::Error` and `std::fmt::Display`
- Use `Result<T, E>` for operations that can fail

```rust
// ✅ From components.rs
#[derive(Debug, Clone)]
pub struct CollisionError;
impl Error for CollisionError {}
impl fmt::Display for CollisionError {
    fn fmt(&self, f: &mut fmt::Formatter) -> fmt::Result {
        write!(f, "overlapping regions not allowed")
    }
}
```

## Main Entry
- `main() -> Result<(), Box<dyn Error>>`
- Map errors: `.map_err(|err| Box::new(err) as Box<dyn Error>)`

## Logging
- Use `log::info!`, `log::error!` (with `pretty_env_logger::init()` in main)
- Fatal engine errors: `error!("FATAL: Unexpected error..."); ActionFollowUp::Exit`

## Graceful Degradation
- When init fails (e.g., audio), continue with fallback: `AudioEngine::dummy(sample_rate)`
- Log the failure but don’t panic
- The user should always be informed of the error and given the option to quit or try and recover
